Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and mince @scallions{2}(minced). Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Blue Cheese Dressing{1.5%oz}, @Sour Cream{2%tbsp}, and a pinch of scallions to taste. Set aside.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tbsp}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine @Ground Turkey{10%oz}, @Frank's Seasoning Blend{14.4%g}, remaining @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, remaining scallions, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Form into two patties (four patties for 4 servings), each slightly wider than a burger bun. TIP: Wet your hands before shaping patties to prevent sticking.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large, preferably nonstick, pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. TIP: If patties begin to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

In the last ~{1-2%minutes} of cooking, evenly top patties with @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup}(shredded); cover pan until cheese melts.

While patties cook, halve and toast @Potato Buns{2}.

Spread bottom buns with a bit of blue cheese sauce. Fill buns with patties, @Crispy Fried Onions{1}, and as much @?Frank's Hot Sauce{1} as you like.

Divide burgers and potato wedges between plates. Serve with remaining blue cheese sauce on the side for dipping.